Marlian president Naira Marley has said he would yet shine whether he’s loved or hated. The “Coming” singer in recent tweets, outlined several reasons why “they” (unnamed individuals), hate him. According to Naira Marley: “They hate me cos they can’t control me, they hate me because they can’t influence me, they hate me because I don’t keep their company, they hate me for being me. Ha!”   New millionaire emerges as D’banj launches Cream Dela…     Social media slowly becoming ‘real life’ – Omoni Oboli     Man accuses Wande Coal, gang of beating elder brother   In a separate tweet, the 31-year-old singer revealed he’s also capable of dishing out hatred to his haters but he’d rather not because he enjoys God’s love. “I can hate too but I’ll rather not, imagine hating someone God loves. You fit no make am again for life,” he added. Wrapping up, the popular street-hop stated: “Love me or hate me I’m still gonna shine.”